arkdown\" v-html=\"entry.post\"></span>"},"startColumn":3,"startLine":3}}}],"message":{"text":"Dynamically rendering arbitrary HTML on your website can be very dangerous because it can easily lead to XSS vulnerabilities. Only use HTML interpolation on trusted content and never on user-provided content."},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.vue.security.audit.xss.templates.avoid-v-html"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"e8c64c45d4bb25f4c60585837b9785fd32d35062dc0f10099b6d526f1fc39c63500608bb2af0d1697388830245615f54a573f9c523fa95c3abc09a31782c4316_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"opengrep-rules/wkhtmltoimage/security/audit/wkhtmltoimage-injection.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":56,"endLine":8,"snippet":{"text":"wkhtmltoimage.generate(input(), { output: 'vuln.jpg' })"},"startColumn":1,"startLine":8}}}],"message":{"text":"If unverified user data can reach the `wkhtmltoimage` it can result in Server-Side Request Forgery vulnerabilities"},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.wkhtmltoimage.security.audit.wkhtmltoimage-injection"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"cae35998da4c879e1432927c559967dfd5263aabae109cf70dc21be098265b90c7548e43d581a9cfe49f59444439de21e464ce6b74d3901a1cd99530d3df07af_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"opengrep-rules/wkhtmltoimage/security/audit/wkhtmltoimage-injection.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":62,"endLine":12,"snippet":{"text":"    wkhtmltoimage.generate(userInput, { output: 'vuln.jpg' })"},"startColumn":5,"startLine":12}}}],"message":{"text":"If unverified user data can reach the `wkhtmltoimage` it can result in Server-Side Request Forgery vulnerabilities"},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.wkhtmltoimage.security.audit.wkhtmltoimage-injection"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"2356edad6e80df0f9dc1e628118148e3384868325d53da937309676c6d4b27a011c0335125cfe46872a7162937e28d3386b63ecfefc67e4b1bf85c76f4fa05af_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"opengrep-rules/wkhtmltopdf/security/audit/wkhtmltopdf-injection.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":45,"endLine":4,"snippet":{"text":"wkhtmltopdf(input(), { output: 'vuln.pdf' })"},"startColumn":1,"startLine":4}}}],"message":{"text":"If unverified user data can reach the `wkhtmltopdf` it can result in Server-Side Request Forgery vulnerabilities"},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.wkhtmltopdf.security.audit.wkhtmltopdf-injection"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"750d65f9ff886e126680dbe1e2752cbec78503c0a69e22af5eba7900a1a83d2e666d88ed9af951b5d0ccdeb8056f2e9c99ece6432812ccb904e53171fa2c8645_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"opengrep-rules/wkhtmltopdf/security/audit/wkhtmltopdf-injection.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":56,"endLine":8,"snippet":{"text":"  return wkhtmltopdf(userInput, { output: 'vuln.pdf' })"},"startColumn":10,"startLine":8}}}],"message":{"text":"If unverified user data can reach the `wkhtmltopdf` it can result in Server-Side Request Forgery vulnerabilities"},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.wkhtmltopdf.security.audit.wkhtmltopdf-injection"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"77dff4e9f84d346185db238f38f45a6265dd9c08f7923b0f20c8d070f1f3674cad2089785d179fb3dbaa3ea0d23ee53dbc812b97ed0198b532444a60ff747de9_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"opengrep-rules/xml2json/security/audit/xml2json-xxe.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":80,"endLine":4,"snippet":{"text":"    const xml2json = require('xml2json')\n    const result = xml2json.toJson(body, { object: true, arrayNotation: true })"},"startColumn":5,"startLine":3}}}],"message":{"text":"If unverified user data can reach the XML Parser it can result in XML External or Internal Entity (XXE) Processing vulnerabilities"},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.xml2json.security.audit.xml2json-xxe"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"a3fec55d56a628653d35566ce23c9ba6241a90b9bfa81a69c756ceeb8c68b761cfcd5ed7f407cffbb2e5a698f374cbcd7f53c0d64afcc9a1e907bcc30a7461c3_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"opengrep-rules/xml2json/security/audit/xml2json-xxe.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":41,"endLine":3,"snippet":{"text":"    const xml2json = require('xml2json')"},"startColumn":22,"startLine":3}}}],"message":{"text":"Lazy loading can complicate code bundling if care is not taken, also `require`s are run synchronously by Node.js. If they are called from within a function, it may block other requests from being handled at a more critical time. The best practice is to `require` modules at the beginning of each file, before and outside of any functions."},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.lang.best-practice.lazy-load-module"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"cb958fba82d61d20e02d3251d522e2024f10ddbff2ab258ecc8699ec137b0f787c96953ae0af17a2048b275e94087a72a87ffd4730cc33d8f4661c5e44d2c510_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"opengrep-rules/xml2json/security/audit/xml2json-xxe.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":41,"endLine":10,"snippet":{"text":"    const xml2json = require('xml2json')"},"startColumn":22,"startLine":10}}}],"message":{"text":"Lazy loading can complicate code bundling if care is not taken, also `require`s are run synchronously by Node.js. If they are called from within a function, it may block other requests from being handled at a more critical time. The best practice is to `require` modules at the beginning of each file, before and outside of any functions."},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.lang.best-practice.lazy-load-module"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"cb958fba82d61d20e02d3251d522e2024f10ddbff2ab258ecc8699ec137b0f787c96953ae0af17a2048b275e94087a72a87ffd4730cc33d8f4661c5e44d2c510_1"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"opengrep-rules/xml2json/security/audit/xml2json-xxe.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":41,"endLine":17,"snippet":{"text":"    const xml2json = require('xml2json')"},"startColumn":22,"startLine":17}}}],"message":{"text":"Lazy loading can complicate code bundling if care is not taken, also `require`s are run synchronously by Node.js. If they are called from within a function, it may block other requests from being handled at a more critical time. The best practice is to `require` modules at the beginning of each file, before and outside of any functions."},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.lang.best-practice.lazy-load-module"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"99e7224f3421f6ae5e693a65ef4965d14840a6ca4b3f3983ef43c9be6cf38f33b8789dbc398c3598f3b4bfd39d84e7612488b0893c2b9136a5328c2408928c4f_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"server.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":22,"endLine":15,"snippet":{"text":"const app = express(); // Web framework to handle routing requests"},"startColumn":7,"startLine":15}}}],"message":{"text":"A CSRF middleware was not detected in your express application. Ensure you are either using one such as `csurf` or `csrf` (see rule references) and/or you are properly doing CSRF validation in your routes with a token or cookies."},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.express.security.audit.express-check-csurf-middleware-usage"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"3a2b807170da64ade0d632359a8be778246ce6bc00a15b26e67b8a958abf17a6121e836249c98000c25a4077a1880ee7a6ea0fb2d4130339555ae6f7507ccceb_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"server.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":7,"endLine":102,"snippet":{"text":"    app.use(session({\n        // genid: (req) => {\n        //    return genuuid() // use UUIDs for session IDs\n        //},\n        secret: cookieSecret,\n        // Both mandatory in Express v4\n        saveUninitialized: true,\n        resave: true\n        /*\n        // Fix for A5 - Security MisConfig\n        // Use generic cookie name\n        key: \"sessionId\",\n        */\n\n        /*\n        // Fix for A3 - XSS\n        // TODO: Add \"maxAge\"\n        cookie: {\n            httpOnly: true\n            // Remember to start an HTTPS server to get this working\n            // secure: true\n        }\n        */\n\n    }));"},"startColumn":13,"startLine":78}}}],"message":{"text":"Don’t use the default session cookie name Using the default session cookie name can open your app to attacks. The security issue posed is similar to X-Powered-By: a potential attacker can use it to fingerprint the server and target attacks accordingly."},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.express.security.audit.express-cookie-session-default-name"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"ba768448a304d2676c0e838b8aa34b0abc1f0b609f9e7adbe2eb5b2e9166e4668c83a5dcb2d981d746ed80a8d5f363ba463b779e57d619f0aa283271cd6255e8_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"server.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":7,"endLine":102,"snippet":{"text":"    app.use(session({\n        // genid: (req) => {\n        //    return genuuid() // use UUIDs for session IDs\n        //},\n        secret: cookieSecret,\n        // Both mandatory in Express v4\n        saveUninitialized: true,\n        resave: true\n        /*\n        // Fix for A5 - Security MisConfig\n        // Use generic cookie name\n        key: \"sessionId\",\n        */\n\n        /*\n        // Fix for A3 - XSS\n        // TODO: Add \"maxAge\"\n        cookie: {\n            httpOnly: true\n            // Remember to start an HTTPS server to get this working\n            // secure: true\n        }\n        */\n\n    }));"},"startColumn":13,"startLine":78}}}],"message":{"text":"Default session middleware settings: `domain` not set. It indicates the domain of the cookie; use it to compare against the domain of the server in which the URL is being requested. If they match, then check the path attribute next."},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.express.security.audit.express-cookie-session-no-domain"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"eb8776a28455614ce4249791ed13a47418cddeae83aeef6f5d4aef7349270ab8bdd7bc9fc0c1beb78b074ed4df5694a35b8580d513dabd114ac87dd86c835d05_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"server.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":7,"endLine":102,"snippet":{"text":"    app.use(session({\n        // genid: (req) => {\n        //    return genuuid() // use UUIDs for session IDs\n        //},\n        secret: cookieSecret,\n        // Both mandatory in Express v4\n        saveUninitialized: true,\n        resave: true\n        /*\n        // Fix for A5 - Security MisConfig\n        // Use generic cookie name\n        key: \"sessionId\",\n        */\n\n        /*\n        // Fix for A3 - XSS\n        // TODO: Add \"maxAge\"\n        cookie: {\n            httpOnly: true\n            // Remember to start an HTTPS server to get this working\n            // secure: true\n        }\n        */\n\n    }));"},"startColumn":13,"startLine":78}}}],"message":{"text":"Default session middleware settings: `expires` not set. Use it to set expiration date for persistent cookies."},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.express.security.audit.express-cookie-session-no-expires"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"f180923d60903c0a6a0f3c7fb5c94f315e444686839ef28cb7018c0f1130ca87a13e682b383f3708543dfe2bd699b745a87f652d6e44499ef1b7c7f3ffe0c50f_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"server.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":7,"endLine":102,"snippet":{"text":"    app.use(session({\n        // genid: (req) => {\n        //    return genuuid() // use UUIDs for session IDs\n        //},\n        secret: cookieSecret,\n        // Both mandatory in Express v4\n        saveUninitialized: true,\n        resave: true\n        /*\n        // Fix for A5 - Security MisConfig\n        // Use generic cookie name\n        key: \"sessionId\",\n        */\n\n        /*\n        // Fix for A3 - XSS\n        // TODO: Add \"maxAge\"\n        cookie: {\n            httpOnly: true\n            // Remember to start an HTTPS server to get this working\n            // secure: true\n        }\n        */\n\n    }));"},"startColumn":13,"startLine":78}}}],"message":{"text":"Default session middleware settings: `httpOnly` not set. It ensures the cookie is sent only over HTTP(S), not client JavaScript, helping to protect against cross-site scripting attacks."},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.express.security.audit.express-cookie-session-no-httponly"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"f467794175c7a554d5de0d5d2ee227c30e8b62a963e21ab54461b91464711ecc18ade6dd634181d21859bc5a708b5611ff77b20b10eb3574caa1ca976ab2b25f_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"server.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":7,"endLine":102,"snippet":{"text":"    app.use(session({\n        // genid: (req) => {\n        //    return genuuid() // use UUIDs for session IDs\n        //},\n        secret: cookieSecret,\n        // Both mandatory in Express v4\n        saveUninitialized: true,\n        resave: true\n        /*\n        // Fix for A5 - Security MisConfig\n        // Use generic cookie name\n        key: \"sessionId\",\n        */\n\n        /*\n        // Fix for A3 - XSS\n        // TODO: Add \"maxAge\"\n        cookie: {\n            httpOnly: true\n            // Remember to start an HTTPS server to get this working\n            // secure: true\n        }\n        */\n\n    }));"},"startColumn":13,"startLine":78}}}],"message":{"text":"Default session middleware settings: `path` not set. It indicates the path of the cookie; use it to compare against the request path. If this and domain match, then send the cookie in the request."},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.express.security.audit.express-cookie-session-no-path"},{"fingerprints":{"matchBasedId/v1":"b66d6f4a2eb1e3a28c51370a7d8a087812ca304ac791687b6e993b5a9cdc194934e22637954fedd9db4c28dea2bfb9f9a9def859ca6fd7be7930c7c02c91118f_0"},"locations":[{"physicalLocation":{"artifactLocation":{"uri":"server.js","uriBaseId":"%SRCROOT%"},"region":{"endColumn":7,"endLine":102,"snippet":{"text":"    app.use(session({\n        // genid: (req) => {\n        //    return genuuid() // use UUIDs for session IDs\n        //},\n        secret: cookieSecret,\n        // Both mandatory in Express v4\n        saveUninitialized: true,\n        resave: true\n        /*\n        // Fix for A5 - Security MisConfig\n        // Use generic cookie name\n        key: \"sessionId\",\n        */\n\n        /*\n        // Fix for A3 - XSS\n        // TODO: Add \"maxAge\"\n        cookie: {\n            httpOnly: true\n            // Remember to start an HTTPS server to get this working\n            // secure: true\n        }\n        */\n\n    }));"},"startColumn":13,"startLine":78}}}],"message":{"text":"Default session middleware settings: `secure` not set. It ensures the browser only sends the cookie over HTTPS."},"properties":{},"ruleId":"opengrep-rules.express.security.audit.express-cookie-session-no-secure"}],"tool":{"driver":{"name":"Opengrep OSS","rules":[{"defaultConfiguration":{"level":"warning"},"fullDescription":{"text":"By setting `allErrors: true` in `Ajv` library, all error objects will be allocated without limit. This allows the attacker to produce a huge number of errors which can lead to denial of service. Do not use `allErrors: true` in production."},"help":{"markdown":"By setting `allErrors: true` in `Ajv` library, all error objects will be allocated without limit. This allows the attacker to produce a huge number of errors which can lead to denial of service. Do not use `allErrors: true` in production.\n\n<b>References:</b>\n - [https://ajv.js.org/options.html#allerrors](https://ajv.js.org/options.html#allerrors)\n","text":"By setting `allErrors: true` in `Ajv` library, all error objects will be allocated without limit. This allows the attacker to produce a huge number of errors which can lead to denial of service. Do not use `allErrors: true` in production."},"id":"opengrep-rules.ajv.security.audit.ajv-allerrors-true","name":"opengrep-rules.ajv.security.audit.ajv-allerrors-true","properties":{"precision":"very-high","tags":["CWE-400: Uncontrolled Resource Consumption","LOW CONFIDENCE","security"]},"shortDescription":{"text":"Opengrep Finding: opengrep-rules.ajv.security.audit.ajv-allerrors-true"}},{"defaultConfiguration":{"level":"note"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Use of angular.element can lead to XSS if user-input is treated as part of the HTML element within `$SINK`. It is recommended to contextually output encode user-input, before inserting into `$SINK`. If the HTML needs to be preserved it is recommended to sanitize the input using $sce.getTrustedHTML or $sanitize."},"help":{"markdown":"Use of angular.element can lead to XSS if user-input is treated as part of the HTML element within `$SINK`. It is recommended to contextually output encode user-input, before inserting into `$SINK`. If the HTML needs to be preserved it is recommended to sanitize the input using $sce.getTrustedHTML or $sanitize.\n\n<b>References:</b>\n - [https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/function/angular.element](https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/function/angular.element)\n - [https://owasp.org/www-chapter-london/assets/slides/OWASPLondon20170727_AngularJS.pdf](https://owasp.org/www-chapter-london/assets/slides/OWASPLondon20170727_AngularJS.pdf)\n","text":"Use of angular.element can lead to XSS if user-input is treated as part of the HTML element within `$SINK`. It is recommended to contextually output encode user-input, before inserting into `$SINK`. If the HTML needs to be preserved it is recommended to sanitize the input using $sce.getTrustedHTML or $sanitize."},"id":"opengrep-rules.angular.security.detect-angular-element-methods","name":"opengrep-rules.angular.security.detect-angular-element-methods","properties":{"precision":"very-high","tags":["CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')","LOW CONFIDENCE","OWASP-A03:2021 - Injection","OWASP-A07:2017 - Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)","security"]},"shortDescription":{"text":"Opengrep Finding: opengrep-rules.angular.security.detect-angular-element-methods"}},{"defaultConfiguration":{"level":"warning"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Use of angular.element can lead to XSS if user-input is treated as part of the HTML element within `$SINK`. It is recommended to contextually output encode user-input, before inserting into `$SINK`. If the HTML needs to be preserved it is recommended to sanitize the input using $sce.getTrustedHTML or $sanitize."},"help":{"markdown":"Use of angular.element can lead to XSS if user-input is treated as part of the HTML element within `$SINK`. It is recommended to contextually output encode user-input, before inserting into `$SINK`. If the HTML needs to be preserved it is recommended to sanitize the input using $sce.getTrustedHTML or $sanitize.\n\n<b>References:</b>\n - [https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/function/angular.element](https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/function/angular.element)\n - [https://owasp.org/www-chapter-london/assets/slides/OWASPLondon20170727_AngularJS.pdf](https://owasp.org/www-chapter-london/assets/slides/OWASPLondon20170727_AngularJS.pdf)\n","text":"Use of angular.element can lead to XSS if user-input is treated as part of the HTML element within `$SINK`. It is recommended to contextually output encode user-input, before inserting into `$SINK`. If the HTML needs to be preserved it is recommended to sanitize the input using $sce.getTrustedHTML or $sanitize."},"id":"opengrep-rules.angular.security.detect-angular-element-taint","name":"opengrep-rules.angular.security.detect-angular-element-taint","properties":{"precision":"very-high","tags":["CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')","MEDIUM CONFIDENCE","OWASP-A03:2021 - Injection","OWASP-A07:2017 - Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)","security"]},"shortDescription":{"text":"Opengrep Finding: opengrep-rules.angular.security.detect-angular-element-taint"}},{"defaultConfiguration":{"level":"error"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Use of $window.location.href can lead to open-redirect if user input is used for redirection."},"help":{"markdown":"Use of $window.location.href can lead to open-redirect if user input is used for redirection.\n\n<b>References:</b>\n - [https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/service/$sce#trustAsJs](https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/service/$sce#trustAsJs)\n - [https://owasp.org/www-chapter-london/assets/slides/OWASPLondon20170727_AngularJS.pdf](https://owasp.org/www-chapter-london/assets/slides/OWASPLondon20170727_AngularJS.pdf)\n","text":"Use of $window.location.href can lead to open-redirect if user input is used for redirection."},"id":"opengrep-rules.angular.security.detect-angular-open-redirect","name":"opengrep-rules.angular.security.detect-angular-open-redirect","properties":{"precision":"very-high","tags":["CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')","LOW CONFIDENCE","OWASP-A03:2021 - Injection","OWASP-A07:2017 - Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)","security"]},"shortDescription":{"text":"Opengrep Finding: opengrep-rules.angular.security.detect-angular-open-redirect"}},{"defaultConfiguration":{"level":"warning"},"fullDescription":{"text":"$sceDelegateProvider allowlisting can introduce security issues if wildcards are used."},"help":{"markdown":"$sceDelegateProvider allowlisting can introduce security issues if wildcards are used.\n\n<b>References:</b>\n - [https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/service/$sce#trustAsJs](https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/service/$sce#trustAsJs)\n - [https://owasp.org/www-chapter-london/assets/slides/OWASPLondon20170727_Angul